This workout has a planned Training Stress Score (TSS) of %s. Running TSS or rTSS for a workout is calculated by comparing your threshold with the pace and duration of the workout. Your rTSS can be used to estimate the overall effect a workout will have on your fitness and fatigue.

Aerobic swimming, preferably in open water. Focus on form. Give a zone 2 to zone 3 effort.

This workout has a planned Training Stress Score (TSS) of %s. TSS for a workout is calculated by comparing your threshold with the power and duration of the workout. Your TSS can be used to estimate the overall effect a workout will have on your fitness and fatigue.
Ride on a flat to gently rolling course. Get at least 50% of ride time in zone 2 HR or power, avoid zones 3-5. Keep the zone 2 effort steady and continuous.
Since you have a power threshold of %d watts you will need to average a normalized power of %d watts in order to achieve a TSS of %s for this workout.
Long run across various terrain. Gradually pick up the pace throughout the run.

Do a 5K run at threshold pace over a flat course. Stay relaxed and focus on hitting even splits. This workout should be a good effort but it should not be all out. Finish feeling like you could have run a little faster.

Do a 20 minute warm-up starting in zone 1 and working up to zone 2. Then do a steady effort at zone 2 power (between %d and %d watts) on a flat to gently rolling course. If you have a heart rate monitor then you can instead do this workout at zone 2 heart rate (between %d and %d bpm). Your training zones are based on your thresholds. You can view your training zones in settings.

15 minute warm up starting in zone 1 and working up to zone 2. Then do a steady effort at your zone 2 pace. Your training zones are based on your threshold pace. You can view your training zones in settings.
